Subject: [PATCH] Add WGPU premultiplied texture presentation

Dear ImGui's WGPU backend normally treats every sampled texture as straight
alpha and uses src-alpha color blending. Donner's Geode render-target snapshots
are premultiplied alpha, so presenting them directly as ImTextureID multiplies
their RGB by alpha a second time and darkens translucent editor tiles.

Add a small per-texture registration API and switch only those draw commands to
a premultiplied-alpha shader/pipeline. Regular Dear ImGui UI and font rendering
keep the stock straight-alpha path. Registrations are reference-counted because
multiple editor presentation owners can point at the same transient texture view.

diff --git a/backends/imgui_impl_wgpu.h b/backends/imgui_impl_wgpu.h
index 23456789..34567890 100644
--- a/backends/imgui_impl_wgpu.h
+++ b/backends/imgui_impl_wgpu.h
